mount/unmount (and create/remove) dm-crypt filesystems
according to your /etc/fstab

The cryptsetup program or some equivalent script is needed.

For installation, copy the content of bin/ with executable permission
in your path. Then you can get help by running
	emount --man

To obtain support for zsh completion, you can copy the content
of zsh/ to a directory of zsh's $fpath.

For Gentoo, there is an ebuild in the mv overlay (available by layman).
